    "texts": [
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Identification features",
            "shortText": "<p>Small, flattened, benthic fish with a broad head and wide mouth fringed with fleshy tentacles. Skin loose and body scaleless. Pectoral fin large and spread laterally. Colour pattern distinctive, light brown with dark brown patches and transverse bars, the banding extending onto pectoral and dorsal fins.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_1_3286",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Adult size",
            "shortText": "<p>Up to 10 cm.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_2_3287",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Distribution",
            "shortText": "<p><u>Global:</u> Endemic to South Africa.</p><p><u>Local/Regional:</u> Saldanha Bay to Eastern Cape.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_3_3288",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Biology",
            "shortText": "<p>Bottom-dwelling and reluctant to swim, usually just moving a short distance if disturbed. Fairly common in rock pools and under boulders and seldom found deeper than 10 m depth. Makes a grunting noise when handled.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_4_3289",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Food / prey",
            "shortText": "<p>Details unknown, but assumed to be a predator of invertebrates.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_5_3290",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Reproduction",
            "shortText": "<p>Details unknown.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_6_3291",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Similar species",
            "shortText": "<p>Easily recognised to group, but a second similar species, the Pleated toadfish <i>Chatrabus felinus</i> (formerly <i>Batrichthys felinus</i>), also occurs in the same region. That species grow considerably larger though (to 19 cm), has larger, bulging eyes, a loose, wrinkled skin and a fat-lipped mouth fringed with small tentacles. Colour dark brown with yellow barring.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_7_3292",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
